Quote: It is a good idea to make the riffles in two sections, as this helps washing up, and there may be occasions when it is necessary to wash up the top set only. <i>Ibid.</i> 32 Washing up on these large claims was complicated and interesting to watch, particularly the final phases when one might see a billy of gold recovered. The length of the sluicing run depended on the richness of the ground, some claims washing up monthly others after several months.
